description:
Appreciate my work? Can you buy me a coffe please :)

Eiza González: Eiza González Reyna is a Mexican actress and singer, born in Caborca, Sonora, Mexico, on January 30, 1990. The daughter of Glenda Reyna, a former model, and Carlos, Eiza studied at the Edron academies and at the American School Foundation, from Mexico City. Her childhood would not be easy, her father died when she was 12 years old in a motorcycle accident and she was diagnosed with attention deficit hyperactivity disorder. Her performance focused on her hyperactivity and she, when she was 14 years old, she was accepted to the CEA, from Televisa. She spent two years there, of the three planned, before being chosen as the protagonist of a new youth telenovela, Lola, érase una vez (2007), which became a phenomenon of popularity in Mexico and Latin America and led to the little actress and singer to the height of fame.
